{# ── Why Nevada ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="why-nevada" aria-labelledby="why-h2">
  <div class="why-nevada__grid">
    <div>
      <header class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why Nevada</span>
        <h2 id="why-h2">The most-mined gold state in the United States.</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="why-nevada__article">
        <p>The Nevada Bureau of Mines and Geology identifies Nevada as the nation&rsquo;s leading gold producer, accounting for most United States gold production in recent annual reporting. The state&rsquo;s modern gold endowment is concentrated in documented mineral trends rather than scattered anecdotes, which is why public MRDS, NBMG, and Mindat records matter to a buyer reviewing a property file.</p>
        <p>The United States Geological Survey describes the Carlin area as containing a wide range of deposit types and notes that continued exploration after the original Carlin discoveries built one of the largest gold endowments on Earth. Separate USGS work across north-central Nevada documents the Battle Mountain&ndash;Eureka and Carlin gold trends as regional-scale mineral alignments.</p>
        <p>The Goldstone portfolio reflects two documented Nevada deposit settings: Lynn Creek Placers, a placer gold occurrence in Eureka County, and Adelaide Mine, a copper-gold-silver-lead skarn occurrence in Humboldt County. Both property records can be checked against Mindat locality pages and USGS MRDS records before a buyer requests the full packet.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside aria-labelledby="why-sources">
      <h3 id="why-sources" class="label" style="margin-bottom: var(--s-4)">Primary sources &amp; references</h3>
      <ul class="source-list">
        <li>
          <a href="https://mrdata.usgs.gov/mrds/" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">USGS Mineral Resources Data System</span>
            <span class="src__desc">U.S. Geological Survey &mdash; authoritative record of past production, deposits, and occurrences.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.usgs.gov/data/mines-mineral-occurrences-and-mining-districts-carlin-area-nevada" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">USGS &mdash; Carlin Area Database</span>
            <span class="src__desc">Mines, mineral occurrences, and mining districts in the Carlin area.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://pubs.usgs.gov/publication/ofr01346" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">USGS &mdash; Carlin and Battle Mountain&ndash;Eureka Trends</span>
            <span class="src__desc">Regional resistivity structure across north-central Nevada gold trends.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://nbmg.unr.edu/" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">Nevada Bureau of Mines and Geology</span>
            <span class="src__desc">University of Nevada, Reno &mdash; state-level geologic mapping and minerals industry reporting.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.mindat.org/loc-60622.html" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">Mindat &mdash; Lynn Creek Placers</span>
            <span class="src__desc">Locality record 60622 &mdash; deposit, mineralogy, history.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.mindat.org/loc-59702.html" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">Mindat &mdash; Adelaide Mine</span>
            <span class="src__desc">Locality record 59702 &mdash; deposit, mineralogy, references.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://minerals.nv.gov/" rel="external noopener" target="_blank">
            <span class="src__title">Nevada Division of Minerals</span>
            <span class="src__desc">State agency tracking active claims, permits, and reclamation.</span>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

